<p>
<p>Anyone can apply to become a volunteer. The starting age may vary but is usually between 16 and 18. There is no upper age limit.

<p>Some Trusts open applications at a specific time. Other Trusts accept applications throughout the year.

<p>When no opportunities are available, some Trusts may ask you to register your interest with them. In other cases, you may need to keep checking their webpage for any openings.

<p>We outline some of the generic processes and timelines here. You can refer to your chosen Trust for more detailed information.

<h3>What applying could look like</h3>
<p>Most times you will need to complete an application form. You may need to include details of your past experience and some character references.

