<h3>Creating an inclusive environment</h3>
<p>We welcome applications from volunteers from all walks of life and backgrounds.

<p>It is our aim to create a service that reflects the diverse communities that we serve.

<p>We will continue to work with those who identify with ethnic minority groups, disabilities, less affluent backgrounds and other protected characteristics to ensure that our service continues to be open to everyone.

<p>If you have any questions, talk to the manager of your volunteering service. They can work with you to see how they can best support you.

<h3>Getting started</h3>
<li>You may need to provide proof of your identity and address.
<li>Depending on your volunteering role, you may need to go through some checks. These could include occupational health and Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) checks.
<li>You may also need to go through some mandatory training on:
<li>equality, diversity and human rights
<li>fire safety
<li>health, safety and welfare
<li>infection prevention and control
<li>information governance</p>


